## Overview\
\'a0\
Active ANCA-associated vasculitis (AAV) requires intensive \
immunosuppressive therapy, but continued treatment after remission \
causes serious harm. Routine markers such as CRP and ANCA lack \
sensitivity and specificity for remission status. This repository \
contains all analysis code, frozen model objects, and reproducibility \
documentation for a multi-stage machine learning pipeline that \
identifies and validates a 7-protein plasma panel (AHSG, CLEC3B, COMP, \
F9, LRG1, MCAM, MRC1) for diagnosing remission in AAV. The panel was \
developed in a discovery cohort using targeted PRM-MS proteomics \
and validated in an independent external cohort and a pooled 60/40 \
re-split.\
\'a0\
